including nursing homes, operating within the state of West Virginia;(2) The Health Care Facility Lookup page is provided to the public for easy access to general information on health care facilities and provides search parameters of facility type, facility name, and county; (3) The contact information provided includes the name of the facility, address, and telephone number; and(4) During a pandemic or large scale emergency it would be beneficial to the citizens of West Virginia to have access to contact information for nursing home medical directors.(b) The Department of Health shall include the name of each medical director for each nursing home on the Health Care Facility Lookup page. NOTE: The purpose of this bill is to provide the citizens of West Virginia with the names of medical directors of nursing homes on the online site maintained by OHFLAC.Strike-throughs indicate language that would be stricken from a heading or the present law Health  underscoring indicates new language that would be added. Bill Status  | Bill Tracking  | Legacy WV Code  | Bulletin Board  | District Maps  | Senate Roster  | House Roster  | Live  | Blog  | Jobs  | Links  | Home This Web site is maintained by the West Virginia Legislature's Office of Reference & Information.  | Terms of Use | Webmaster | © 2025 West Virginia Legislature ** Print On Demand Name: Email: Phone:


